io.sphere.sdk.zones

Interface Zone

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CreationTimestamped, Identifiable<Zone>, Referenceable<Zone>, Resource<Zone>, ResourceIdentifiable<Zone>, ResourceView<Zone,Zone>, Timestamped, Versioned<Zone>

    public interface Zone
extends Resource<Zone>
    Zones define Shipping Rates for a set of Locations.
    See Also:
    ZoneCreateCommand, ZoneUpdateCommand, ZoneDeleteCommand, ZoneQuery, ZoneByIdGet, ShippingMethod.getZones(), ZoneRate.getZone()

      • contains

        default boolean contains(com.neovisionaries.i18n.CountryCode countryCode)
        Looks up the locations and checks if the country is present. It does not matter if the location has a state specified.
        Parameters:
        countryCode - the country to search for
        Returns:
        true if the country is somehow in the locations.

      • referenceOfId

        static Reference<Zone> referenceOfId(String id)
        Creates a reference for one item of this class by a known ID.

        An example for categories but this applies for other resources, too:

        final String categoryIdFromFormOrSession = "84ac4271-0fec-49d0-9fee-55586c565c58";
final Reference<Category> categoryReference = Category.referenceOfId(categoryIdFromFormOrSession);
assertThat(categoryReference.getId()).isEqualTo(categoryIdFromFormOrSession);

        See the test code.

        If you already have a resource object, then use toReference() instead:

        final Category category = getCategory1();
final Reference<Category> categoryReference = category.toReference();
assertThat(category.getId()).isEqualTo(categoryReference.getId());

        See the test code.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the resource which should be referenced.
        Returns:
        reference
